identifications.body:
@benjamincejp
Morpho peleides is the archaic name for the Trans-Andean populations of M. helenor.  M. peleides proper is now considered to be a ssp. of M. helenor and occurs in extreme s. Panama-Colombia.  All previous subspecies of M. peleides in Central America have been reclassified as subspecies of M. helenor.  Most populations from Nicaragua to Panama belong to M. narcissus (incl. ssp. carillensis, dufeki, guanacastensis, etc.).
